per liberos] Antonius sent his son (c. 13) and Lepidus a son also, as hostages to the conspirators in the Capitol, before they came down to the sitting of the senate on the 18th of March. Antonius sent only one of his sons, but it is usual to speak of one child thus. 11 was a son by Fulvia, a mere child (Phil. ii. 8. 36).
